I don't know what the plan will be, I don't deal directly with these issues.
In fact, the economy for Russia in Libya is not important.
We are, in fact, engaged in peacemaking work.
The main thing for us is to stop the bloodshed, to help the Libyans agree with each other so that they can establish order and Libya has ceased to be a favourable environment for the development of terrorism.
For Russia, this is the main task - to help the Libyan people and to expel terrorists from there.
Do you have data on the presence in Libya (now or before) of radical militants from Russia or other countries of the former USSR?
